Creates and implements solutions from initial concept to fully tested production and communicates results to a broad range of audiences. Expert in the use of all data types, statistical and quantitative analysis, explanatory and high- complexity predictive modeling and fact-based management to drive decision making. Leads cross functional projects and programs. Routinely works on multiple highly complex assignments concurrently.

Essential Functions







Bachelor's degree in a quantitative discipline required. A Master's degree in a related field may off set two years of the required experience. Related experience may offset degree requirements and related education/degree may offset experience requirements.



Seven (7) years experience required in solving analytics problems through the application of data science techniques or work experience in measurement and analysis, quantitative business problem solving, solutions implementation, operations analysis, marketing analysis, simulation development and/or predictive analytics.

Experience should include using most of the following:



Demonstrated superior analytical skills with diverse analytics, data types and statistical software and applications.

Outstanding interpersonal skills, written, and oral communication skill. Proven leadership skills.

Ability to design mathematical algorithms that employ predictive and machine learning models.

Ability to understand how new tools/methodology can be implemented to solve business problems.

Ability to read, analyze, and interpret common technical journals, reports, and related documents.

Ability to effectively present information to management, end users, co-workers, or vendors.

Ability to perform complex tasks with limited direction.

Proficient with MS office applications.

Overview

Microsoft's mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

The Senior Cloud Solution Architect is part of the Development Squad organization working with Latin America Area team of software engineers that jointly develops strategic projects with customers in the region. The co-development happens in the customer environment and targets a business problem prioritized with Latin American country leaders and customer executives. It aims to materialize innovative scenarios for the customers and contribute to their digital transformation. The team leverages Microsoft Cloud platform and works with patterns such as Cloud Native, microservices applications, data pipelines, Open AI integration and related workloads for Frontier solutions.

The Latin America Development Squad Organization is distributed across all the continent, its diverse with multicultural experienced professionals, and you will be working with teammates in the USA and LATAM. The position is fully remote as you will be working with customers across multiple countries in Mexico, Caribbean, Central America and South America. We are looking at both seasonal engineering roles or customer-facing roles in consulting with proven experience and active technical, design and coding experience.





Other Requirements

There is a different range applicable to specific work locations, within the San Francisco Bay area and New York City metropolitan area, and the base pay range for this role in those locations is USD $137,600 - $222,600 per year.
